scaledmarkets.dabl.exec

Class LocalRepo

  • java.lang.Object
    • scaledmarkets.dabl.exec.LocalRepo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Repo

    public class LocalRepo
extends java.lang.Object
implements Repo
    A DABL "local repository" is a file storage area (e.g., directory) available on the host system that is running the DABL processor. Its purpose is to store intermediate build artifacts. A local repository is isolated from other local repositories.
